This article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on May 27, 2009. The memorandum addresses the classification and handling of classified and controlled unclassified information within the government. The President directs a review of Executive Order 12958, which pertains to classified national security information, and requests recommendations for revisions to the order. The memorandum also discusses the need for a standardized framework for designating and handling sensitive but unclassified information (SBU) and the establishment of a single, comprehensive framework for controlled unclassified information (CUI). An Interagency Task Force on CUI is created to review current procedures and make recommendations. The memorandum emphasizes the importance of openness and transparency in government while also protecting privacy and national security. The heads of agencies are instructed to assist the Task Force, and the memorandum is subject to applicable law and appropriations. The Attorney General is authorized to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.